Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers
MANILA , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Philippine newspapers Monday .
The Manila Bulletin :
-- Police and volunteers intensified operations Sunday to rescue 10 miners in a Southern Philippine mountain for five days following a landslide .
Business World :
-- Japan will set up a 3 billion U.S. dollar special lending window within the Asian Development Bank that will provide guarantee cover for the bond issues of five troubled Asian economies .
The Philippine Star :
-- Philippine President Joseph Estrada rejected Sunday former First Lady Imelda Marcos ' appeal for his administration 's help in recovering her family 's assets from her late husband 's cronies .
